# .dockerignore Template

This file specifies which files and directories should be excluded from the Docker build context.

## Basic .dockerignore

```
# Version control
.git
.gitignore

# Dependencies
node_modules
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
env
venv
.venv
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Runtime data
pids
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# Coverage directory used by tools like istanbul
coverage
.nyc_output

# Dependency directories
jspm_packages/

# Optional npm cache directory
.npm

# Optional REPL history
.node_repl_history

# Output of 'npm pack'
*.tgz

# Yarn Integrity file
.yarn-integrity

# dotenv environment variables file
.env
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# IDE files
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Build outputs
dist
build
.next
.nuxt
.cache

# Documentation
README.md
docs/
*.md

# Test files
test/
tests/
*.test.js
*.spec.js
__tests__/

# Docker files
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore

# CI/CD
.github/
.gitlab-ci.yml
.travis.yml
```

## Language-Specific Examples

### For Node.js Projects
```
node_modules
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm
.yarn-integrity
.env
coverage/
.nyc_output/
.cache/
dist/
build/
```

### For Python Projects
```
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
env/
venv/
.venv/
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt
.tox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.log
.env
```

### For Go Projects
```
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool
*.out

# Dependency directories
vendor/
```

### For Java/Maven Projects
```
target/
pom.xml.tag
pom.xml.releaseBackup
pom.xml.versionsBackup
pom.xml.next
release.properties
dependency-reduced-pom.xml
buildNumber.properties
.mvn/timing.properties
.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar
```